1         Overview

1.1        Changes in This Version

The following examples have been updated to illustrate changes within the Medicare component of the HR-XML Enrollment schema:

  • Section 3.2.3, Example B3 – Spouse adds Medicare supplemental enrollment
  • Section 3.4.3, Example D3— Employee becomes Medicare eligible
  • Section 3.4.4, Example D4— Spouse becomes Medicare eligible


This example has been added:

  • Section 3.4.5, Example D5— Bernadette’s spouse enrolls in Medicare Part D and loses subsidy

The examples distributed in the prior release remain valid against the revised specification. However, read the Enrollment specification document (see Section 5, Appendix B – Related Documents) for important information about deprecated poritions of the schema, including some portions of the Medicare component.

1.2        Objective

Several benefits providers and their trading partners created test transactions using the Enrollment schema. This document contains descriptions and XML examples for a variety of the enrollment scenarios, based on the test results.

These examples should be reviewed in conjunction with the Enrollment specification (see Appendix B – Related Documents).

2         Trading Partner Roles

The Benefits Enrollment schema supports the exchange of enrollment information between trading partners.  Trading partners may be large employers, HR software vendors, third party administrators, or insurance carriers.

The role of the trading partner within the context of the Benefits Enrollment schema is to communicate and/or receive benefit enrollment information as it relates to a subscriber or dependent. 


3         Reference Examples

3.1        Example A

Joe Thompson is a new hire at Computer Company in their Chicago office.  His date of hire is 01/01/2004 and he is immediately eligibile for his health & welfare benefits.  Joe elects coverage under the HMO option with 'You Only' coverage.

Example A1— Simple Tier Enrollment

On 01/01/2004 Joe elects coverage under the HMO option with 'You Only' coverage.

Example A2 – Add Dependents

On 02/01/2004 Joe gets married and adds his spouse and a child to coverage.  He now has 'Employee + Family' coverage.

Example A3 – Add Dependent to existing family

On 03/01/2004 Joe adds another child to his coverage, but the CoverageLevel remains unchanged.

Example A4 – Terminate Dependent

On 04/01/2004 Joe drops one child from coverage, but the CoverageLevel remains unchanged.

Example A5 – Terminate Dependent

On 5/1/2004 Joe drops the remaining child from coverage.  The CoverageLevel is now 'Employee + Spouse.'

Example A6 – Simple Termination

On 5/31/20004 Joe is terminated from his position with Computer Company.  Coverage for Joe and his spouse is terminated.

Example A7 – Simple Enrollment with COBRA Elements

Joe elects COBRA coverage for him and his spouse and pays for the first month of coverage.  A reinstatement is processed with simple COBRA elements, with no lapse in coverage.

3.1.1          Example A1 - Simple Tier Enrollment

On 01/01/2004 Joe elects coverage under the HMO option with 'You Only' coverage.

 

<Enrollment transactionType="Change" creationDate="2004-01-20T17:25:03-05:00" originatorId="382235791" originatorName="Hewitt Associates LLC" baselineDate="2004-01-29" recipientId="411289245 ">

 

 

 

       <Organization organizationName="5977 ">

 

 

             <BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate>

                    <OrganizationName>Hewitt Associates LLC</OrganizationName>

                    <EntityRole>Third Party Administrator</EntityRole>

                    <IdentificationCode>

                           <IdValue name="Mutually Defined">382235791</IdValue>

                    </IdentificationCode>

             </BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate>

 

             <Subscriber>

                    <SubscriberType>

                           <SubscriberTypeCode>Employment</SubscriberTypeCode>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </SubscriberType>

                    <Person>

                           <IdentificationCode>

                                 <IdValue name="SocialSecurityNumber">536403123</IdValue>

                           </IdentificationCode>

                           <PersonName>

                                 <GivenName>JOE</GivenName>

                                 <MiddleName/>

                                 <FamilyName>THOMPSON</FamilyName>

                           </PersonName>

                           <Gender>1</Gender>

                           <DateOfBirth>1970-06-22</DateOfBirth>

                           <ContactInformation>

                                 <Use>personal</Use>

                                 <PostalAddress type="streetAddress">

                                        <CountryCode>US</CountryCode>

                                        <PostalCode>61043</PostalCode>

                                        <Region>IL</Region>

                                        <Municipality>OAKWOOD</Municipality>

                                        <DeliveryAddress>

                                               <AddressLine>143 MAIN ST.</AddressLine>

                                               <AddressLine/>

                                               <AddressLine/>

                                        </DeliveryAddress>

                                 </PostalAddress>

                           </ContactInformation>

                    </Person>

 

                    <Coverage>

                           <TierCoverage type="Health">

                                 <TransactionCode>Add</TransactionCode>

                                 <ElectedPlanCode>11</ElectedPlanCode>

                                 <GroupNumber>022574900320032TTXX</GroupNumber>

                                 <COBRAStatus>non-COBRA</COBRAStatus>

                                 <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee Only</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                                 <EligibilityPostalCode>61043</EligibilityPostalCode>

                           </TierCoverage>

                    </Coverage>

 

                    <Employment employeeId="428408">

                           <EmploymentStatus>

                                 <EmploymentStatusCode>Active</EmploymentStatusCode>

                                 <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                           </EmploymentStatus>

                           <HireDate>2004-01-01</HireDate>

                    </Employment>

                    <BenefitReportingInformation>

                           <BenefitReportingType>Reporting Field 1</BenefitReportingType>

                           <BenefitReportingValue>0032</BenefitReportingValue>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </BenefitReportingInformation>

                    <BenefitReportingInformation>

                           <BenefitReportingType>Reporting Field 2</BenefitReportingType>

                           <BenefitReportingValue>001278</BenefitReportingValue>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </BenefitReportingInformation>

                    <BenefitReportingInformation>

                           <BenefitReportingType>Reporting Field 3</BenefitReportingType>

                           <BenefitReportingValue>TF1</BenefitReportingValue>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </BenefitReportingInformation>

                    <BenefitReportingInformation>

                           <BenefitReportingType>Reporting Field 4</BenefitReportingType>

                           <BenefitReportingValue>428408</BenefitReportingValue>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </BenefitReportingInformation>

                    <BenefitReportingInformation>

                           <BenefitReportingType>Reporting Field 5</BenefitReportingType>

                           <BenefitReportingValue>A4310</BenefitReportingValue>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </BenefitReportingInformation>

                    <BenefitReportingInformation>

                           <BenefitReportingType>Reporting Field 6</BenefitReportingType>

                           <BenefitReportingValue>TSOP042</BenefitReportingValue>

                           <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                    </BenefitReportingInformation>

             </Subscriber>

 

             <OrganizationId>

                    <IdValue>COMP</IdValue>

             </OrganizationId>

       </Organization>

</Enrollment>

     

 

Begin Enrollment.  The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-01-20T17:25:03-05:00”.

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “5977”.

Begin BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate:  The BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate element encapsulates data about the outsourcing entity.  It contains the organizationName “Hewitt Associates LLC”, and describes the entity as a “Third Party Administrator” with an employer generated ID code of “382235791”.

End BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant and any dependents.  Each family is encapsulated within one Subscriber element.

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

Joe’s SSN is 536-40-3123

 

 

 

 

 

 

Joe’s Date of Birth is 1970-06-22

 

 

Joe’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

 

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

This transaction is adding Joe to Health coverage.  He is enrolled in GroupNumber 022574900320032TTXX.  Joe is Non-COBRA.  He has “Employee Only” coverage.

 

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

 

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing Joe’s employment statuses.

Joe is an Active employee.

 

 He was hired on 2004-01-01.

End Employment

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Subscriber

 

 

OrganizationId is “COMP”

 

End Organization

End Enrollment:  The transaction is complete.

Begin Enrollment. The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-02-03T17:45:40-05:00”.

 

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “5977”.

 

Begin BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate:  The BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate element encapsulates data about the outsourcing entity.  It contains the organizationName “Hewitt Associates LLC”, and describes the entity as a “Third Party Administrator” with an employer generated ID code of “382235791”.

End BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate

 

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant and any dependents.  Each family is encapsulated within one Subscriber element.

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

Joe’s SSN is 536-40-3123

 

 

 

 

 

 

Joe’s Date of Birth is 1970-06-22

 

 

Joe’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

This is a ‘Change’ transaction.  Joe has already been sent previously on an ‘Add’ transaction.

 

 

Joe now has ‘Family’ coverage as of 2004-02-01.

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing Joe’s employment statuses.

Joe is an Active employee.  He was hired on 2004-01-01.

 

End Employment

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Child’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

 

 

The dependent’s name is Sahriya Thompson. Her social security number is 518-59-5872.

 

 

 

Sahriya’s Date of Birth is 2000-05-04.

 

 

Sahriya’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

Sahriya is added to Health coverage. She is in GroupNumber 022574900320032TTXX.  Sahriya is non-COBRA.

Sahriya’s CoverageLevelCode is ‘Family’.

Sahriya’s coverage Start Date is 2004-02-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Spouse’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

 

 

The dependent’s name is Mary Thompson. Her social security number is 444-40-3123.

 

 

 

Mary’s Date of Birth is 1975-06-25.

 

 

Mary’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

Mary is added to Health coverage. She is in GroupNumber 022574900320032TTXX.  Mary is non-COBRA.

Mary’s CoverageLevelCode is ‘Family’.

Mary’s coverage Start Date is 2004-02-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

End Subscriber

 

OrganizationId is “COMP”

 

End Organization

End Enrollment: The Enrollment transaction is complete.

Begin Enrollment. The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-02-03T17:45:40-05:00”.

 

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “5977”.

 

Begin BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate:  The BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate element encapsulates data about the outsourcing entity.  It contains the organizationName “Hewitt Associates LLC”, and describes the entity as a “Third Party Administrator” with an employer generated ID code of “382235791”.

End BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate

 

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant and any dependents.  Each family is encapsulated within one Subscriber element.

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

Joe’s SSN is 536-40-3123

 

 

 

 

 

 

Joe’s Date of Birth is 1970-06-22

 

 

Joe’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

This is a ‘Change’ transaction.  Joe has already been sent previously on an ‘Add’ transaction.

 

 

Joe still has ‘Family’ coverage as of 2004-02-01.

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing Joe’s employment statuses.

Joe is an Active employee.  He was hired on 2004-01-01.

 

End Employment

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Child’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

 

 

The dependent’s name is Sahriya Thompson. Her social security number is 518-59-5872.

 

 

 

Sahriya’s Date of Birth is 2000-05-04.

 

 

Sahriya’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

This is a ‘Change’ transaction.  Sahriya has already been sent previously on an ‘Add’ transaction.

 

Sahriya’s CoverageLevelCode is still ‘Family’.

Sahriya’s coverage Start Date is 2004-02-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Spouse’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

Begin Enrollment. The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-02-03T17:45:40-05:00”.

 

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “5977”.

 

Begin BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate:  The BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate element encapsulates data about the outsourcing entity.  It contains the organizationName “Hewitt Associates LLC”, and describes the entity as a “Third Party Administrator” with an employer generated ID code of “382235791”.

End BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate

 

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant and any dependents.  Each family is encapsulated within one Subscriber element.

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

Joe’s SSN is 536-40-3123

 

 

 

 

 

 

Joe’s Date of Birth is 1970-06-22

 

 

Joe’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

This is a ‘Change’ transaction.  Joe has already been sent previously on an ‘Add’ transaction.

 

 

Joe changed coverage to ‘Employee and Spouse’ as of 2004-05-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing Joe’s employment statuses.

Joe is an Active employee.  He was hired on 2004-01-01.

 

End Employment

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Child’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

 

 

The dependent’s name is Sahriya Thompson. Her social security number is 518-59-5872.

 

 

 

Sahriya’s Date of Birth is 2000-05-04.

 

 

Sahriya’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

 

 

Sahriya’s Health coverage is terminated on 2004-04-30.

 

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Spouse’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

Mary’s CoverageLevelCode is ‘Employee and Spouse’ effective 2004-05-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

Begin Enrollment. The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2001-11-15T01:00:00-09:00”.

Joe’s SSN is 536-40-3123

 

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “5977”.

 

Begin BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate:  The BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate element encapsulates data about the outsourcing entity.  It contains the organizationName “Hewitt Associates LLC”, and describes the entity as a “Third Party Administrator” with an employer generated ID code of “382235791”.

End BenefitsAdministrativeAffiliate

 

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant and any dependents.  Each family is encapsulated within one Subscriber element.

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Joe’s address is 143 Main Street, Oakwood, IL 61043.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

Joe enrolls in the COBRA Health coverage effective 2004-01-01. He is enrolled in a new GroupNumber 022574900320032TTXX. 

 

Joe’s COBRA coverage starts on 2004-06-01.

 

He is qualified for COBRA coverage on 2004-06-01.

 

 

 

Joe enrolls with ‘Employee and Spouse’ coverage effective 2004-06-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing Joe’s employment statuses.

Joe is terminated on 2001-10-31.

SUNEEL – ditto on the termination info.

 

End Employment

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

Begin Dependent: The Dependent element encapsulates all coverage and indicative data about the dependent.  The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Spouse’.

Begin Person:  Dependent also has a Person element that can contain  the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

The dependent, Mary Thompson’s SSN is 256-49-3126.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

Mary enrolls in the COBRA Health coverage effective 2004-01-01. She is enrolled in a new GroupNumber 022574900320032TTXX. 

 

Mary enrolls with ‘Employee and Spouse’ coverage effective 2004-06-01.

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

End Subscriber

 

OrganizationId is “COMP”

 

End Organization

End Enrollment: The Enrollment transaction is complete.

3.2        Example B

Jerry Carmack is employed with Perry & Sons construction. He and his wife, Reba Carmack, are enrolled in a self-insured medical plan from his company.  Jerry and Reba are very close to retirement age. Perry & Sons' medical plan offers coverage to a surviving spouse for the remainder of his or her life.

Example B1– Death of employee

On August 16, 2001, Jerry dies and all benefits are terminated

Example B2 – Surviving spouse enrollment

Reba selects the surviving spouse option of the medical plan after Jerry’s death.

Example B3 – Spouse adds Medicare supplemental enrollment

Reba becomes eligible for Medicare and chooses a supplemental Medicare plan to replace her existing medical coverage.

3.3        Example C

Max Smart is employed with Information and Emergency Company.  He and his wife, Kimberly and two children Cathy and Jonathan are enrolled in the company's health plan.  Cathy is QMCSO dependent and does not live with the family.  Jonathan is going to go to school in a different state.  Max's company will only allow children that are students remain on the policy until their 25th birthday.

 

Example C1 – Simple enrollment with QMCSO dependent

Max elects family coverage (EE + family) with a QMCSO (qualified minor) dependent

Example C2 – Dependent becomes full-time student

Dependent child Jonathan becomes a full-time student and now lives in another state, but the CoverageLevel remains unchanged.

Example C3 – Dependent ages out

Dependent Jonathan ages out, student becomes older than client provisions/state law allows. CoverageLevel remains unchanged.

Begin Enrollment.  The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-01-20T17:25:03-05:00”.

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “Information and Emergency”.

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant and any dependents.  Each family is encapsulated within one Subscriber element.

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

Max’s SSN is 333-11-1111.

 

 

 

 

 

 

Max’s Date of Birth is 1965-12-10

 

Max’s address is 86 Sole Road, Erie, CO, 80516.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

This is a ‘Change’ transaction.  Max has already been sent previously on an ‘Add’ transaction.

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing Max’s employment statuses.

Max is an Active employee. 

 

He was hired on 2000-03-06.

End Employment

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Child’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

 

 

The dependent’s name is Cathy Smart.

 

 

 

Cathy’s Date of Birth is 2003-10-28.

 

Cathy’s address is 503 Pine Circle, Denver, CO 80522.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

Cathy is added to Health coverage. She is in GroupNumber 012345600140014TTRX.  Cathy is non-COBRA.

Cathy’s CoverageLevelCode is ‘Family’.

Cathy’s coverage Start Date is 2003-10-28.

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Child’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

Jonathan’s address is 86 Sole Road, Erie, CO, 80516.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

This is a ‘Change’ transaction.  Jonathan has already been sent previously on an ‘Add’ transaction.

 

Jonathan’s CoverageLevelCode is ‘Family’.

His coverage Start Date is 2003-10-28.

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Spouse’.

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

Cathy is added to Health coverage. She is in GroupNumber 012345600140014TTRX.  Cathy is non-COBRA.

Cathy’s CoverageLevelCode is ‘Family’.

Cathy’s coverage Start Date is 2003-10-28.

End Coverage

3.4        Example D

Bernadette Kleghorn is employed with Example Corporation.  She and her husband Jacob are enrolled in the company's health plan.  When Bernadette retires she changes to a retired version of the health plan. When she becomes eligible, Bernadette enrolls in Medicare. When Jacob is eligible, he also enrolls in Medicare.

Example D1 - Simple tier enrollment

Bernadette Kleghorn and her husband enroll in the HMO offered by her company effective 1/1/2000.

Example D2 – Employee retires

On 2/16/2004, Bernadette retired and was changed into a retiree version of the HMO plan.

Example D3 – Retiree Medicare enrollment

On 2/16/2007, Bernadette turned 65 and went on Medicare (also enrolling in her company's Medicare Risk plan). Her husband remained enrolled in the HMO plan.

Example D4 – Spouse Medicare enrollment

On 10/2/2008, Bernadette's husband joined her on Medicare.

3.7        Example G

Alexander Petrinski is employed with Example Corporation and is enrolled in the company's health plan.  Alexander joins the witness protection plan, changing his gender, SSN, birthdate, address and name to Lisa Langford. Health plan coverage does not change. When Lisa leaves Example Corporation, her health covereage is terminated. Later, Lisa’s employer realizes the termination date is incorrect and changes it.

Example G1 – Simple tier enrollment

A. Petrinski enrolls in the HMO offered by his company effective 1/1/2003.

Example G2 – Witness Protection Program changes

Mr. Petrinski has a name, SSN, gender, birthdate, and address change and becomes Ms. Lisa Langford.

Example G3 – Termination of enrollment

Ms. Langford terminates coverage effective 6/1/2004.

Example G4 – Revision of termination date

Ms. Langford's employer discovers an error in the termination date of her enrollment and changes the termination date to 5/1/2004.

                                 <EndDate>2004-06-01</EndDate>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee Only</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2003-01-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                           </TierCoverage>

                    </Coverage>

             </Subscriber>

       </Organization>

</Enrollment>

 

 

Begin Enrollment.  The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-01-20T17:25:03-05:00”.

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “Example Corporation”.

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant. 

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

Lisa Lanford’s SSN is 999-11-2233.

 

 

 

 

 

Lisa is female and her date of birth is 1951-07-14

 

Lisa’s address is 3011 Carrington Way, Marietta, GA, 30067.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

Lisa terminates her HMO coverage effective 2004-06-01.

 

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Subscriber

End Organization

End Enrollment

3.8        Example H

Lawrence Benjamen (L.B.) Preston is employed with Example Corporation. He is enrolled in the company's health and dental plans.  L.B. cancels his dental coverage. Retroactively, he changes the dental coverage to ‘Employee and Spouse’ and adds his wife Shelley to the dental plan.

Example H1 – Tier enrollment in multiple plans

L. B. Preston enrolls in Medical and Dental effective 1/1/2004.

Example H2 – Terminate Dental coverage

Effective 5/1/2004, L. B. drops dental coverage but keeps medical coverage.

Example H3 – Change in Dental coverage level

Effective 4/1/2004, L. B. changes his coverage level and adds a spouse. His enrollment (and his spouse's enrollment) should still terminate on 5/1/2004.

3.8.1          Example H1 – Tier enrollment in multiple plans

 

<Enrollment creationDate="2004-04-01T13:20:00-05:00">

 

 

 

 

       <Organization organizationName="Example Corporation">

 

 

             <Subscriber>

                    <SubscriberType>

                           <SubscriberTypeCode>Employment</SubscriberTypeCode>

                    </SubscriberType>

 

                    <Person>

                           <IdentificationCode>

                                 <IdValue name="Social Security Number">999-34-5678</IdValue>

                           </IdentificationCode>

                           <PersonName>

                                 <GivenName>Lawrence</GivenName>

                                 <MiddleName>Benjamin</MiddleName>

                                 <FamilyName>Preston</FamilyName>

                           </PersonName>

                           <Gender>1</Gender>

                           <DateOfBirth>1968-04-02</DateOfBirth>

                           <PostalAddress>

                                 <CountryCode>US</CountryCode>

                                 <PostalCode>90038</PostalCode>

                                 <Region>CA</Region>

                                 <Municipality>Vine City</Municipality>

                                 <DeliveryAddress>

                                        <AddressLine>1897B Vapor Drive</AddressLine>

                                 </DeliveryAddress>

                           </PostalAddress>

                    </Person>

                    <Coverage>

                           <TierCoverage type="Health Maintenance Organization">

                                 <GroupNumber>741564M</GroupNumber>

                                 <COBRAStatus>non-COBRA</COBRAStatus>

                                 <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee Only</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                           </TierCoverage>

                           <TierCoverage type="Dental">

                                 <GroupNumber>741564D</GroupNumber>

                                 <COBRAStatus>non-COBRA</COBRAStatus>

                                 <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee Only</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                           </TierCoverage>

                    </Coverage>

                    <Employment>

                           <EmploymentStatus>

                                 <EmploymentStatusCode>Active</EmploymentStatusCode>

                                 <StartDate>1999-04-14</StartDate>

                           </EmploymentStatus>

                    </Employment>

             </Subscriber>

       </Organization>

</Enrollment>

 

 

Begin Enrollment.  The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-01-20T17:25:03-05:00”.

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “Example Corporation”.

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant. 

 

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

L.B. Preston’s SSN is 999-34-5678.

 

 

 

 

 

L.B. is male and his date of birth is 1968-04-02.

 

His address is 1897B Vapor Drive, Vine City, CA, 90038

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

L.B. is enrolled in the ‘Employee Only’ HMO plan effective 2004-01-01.

 

 

 

 

 

L.B. is enrolled in the ‘Employee Only’ Dental plan effective 2004-01-01.

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing L.B’s employment statuses.

L.B is an Active employee.

 

End Employment

End Subscriber

End Organization

End Enrollment

3.8.3          Example H3 – Change in Dental coverage level

Effective 4/1/2004, L. B. changes his coverage level and adds a spouse. His enrollment (and his spouse's enrollment) should still terminate on 5/1/2004.

 

<Enrollment creationDate="2004-04-01T13:20:00-05:00">

 

 

 

 

       <Organization organizationName="Example Corporation">

 

 

             <Subscriber>

                    <SubscriberType>

                           <SubscriberTypeCode>Employment</SubscriberTypeCode>

                    </SubscriberType>

                    <Person>

                           <IdentificationCode>

                                  <IdValue name="Social Security Number">999-34-5678</IdValue>

                           </IdentificationCode>

                           <PersonName>

                                 <GivenName>Lawrence</GivenName>

                                 <MiddleName>Benjamin</MiddleName>

                                 <FamilyName>Preston</FamilyName>

                           </PersonName>

                           <Gender>1</Gender>

                           <DateOfBirth>1968-04-02</DateOfBirth>

                           <PostalAddress>

                                 <CountryCode>US</CountryCode>

                                 <PostalCode>90038</PostalCode>

                                 <Region>CA</Region>

                                 <Municipality>Vine City</Municipality>

                                 <DeliveryAddress>

                                        <AddressLine>1897B Vapor Drive</AddressLine>

                                 </DeliveryAddress>

                           </PostalAddress>

                    </Person>

                    <Coverage>

                           <TierCoverage type="Health Maintenance Organization">

                                 <GroupNumber>741564M</GroupNumber>

                                 <COBRAStatus>non-COBRA</COBRAStatus>

                                 <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee Only</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                           </TierCoverage>

                           <TierCoverage type="Dental">

                                 <GroupNumber>741564D</GroupNumber>

                                 <COBRAStatus>non-COBRA</COBRAStatus>

                                 <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 <EndDate>2004-05-01</EndDate>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee Only</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2004-01-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                                 <CoverageLevel>

                                        <CoverageLevelCode>Employee and Spouse</CoverageLevelCode>

                                        <StartDate>2004-04-01</StartDate>

                                 </CoverageLevel>

                           </TierCoverage>

                    </Coverage>

                    <Employment>

                           <EmploymentStatus>

                                 <EmploymentStatusCode>Active</EmploymentStatusCode>

                                 <StartDate>1999-04-14</StartDate>

                           </EmploymentStatus>

                    </Employment>

                    <Dependent relationshipCode="Spouse">

 

 

                           <Person>

                                 <IdentificationCode>

                                        <IdValue name="Social Security Number">999-51-2346</IdValue>

                                  </IdentificationCode>

                                 <PersonName>

                                        <GivenName>Shelley</GivenName>

                                        <FamilyName>Preston</FamilyName>

                                 </PersonName>

                                 <Gender>2</Gender>

                                 <DateOfBirth>1970-10-25</DateOfBirth>

                           </Person>

                           <Coverage>

                                 <TierCoverage type="Dental">

                                        <GroupNumber>741564D</GroupNumber>

                                        <COBRAStatus>non-COBRA</COBRAStatus>

                                        <StartDate>2004-04-01</StartDate>

                                        <EndDate>2004-05-01</EndDate>

                                        <CoverageLevel>

                                               <CoverageLevelCode>Employee and Spouse</CoverageLevelCode>

                                               <StartDate>2004-04-01</StartDate>

                                        </CoverageLevel>

                                 </TierCoverage>

                           </Coverage>

                    </Dependent>

             </Subscriber>

       </Organization>

</Enrollment>

 

 

Begin Enrollment.  The root element is the Enrollment element.  This element encapsulates the entire enrollment transaction.  The creationDate of this enrollment transaction is “2004-01-20T17:25:03-05:00”.

Begin Organization:  The Organization element contains the organizationName “Example Corporation”.

Begin Subscriber:  The Subscriber element encapsulates all person and enrollment data about the participant. 

 

Begin Person:  The Person element contains indicative data about each member, as well as contact information.

L.B. Preston’s SSN is 999-34-5678.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage element encapsulates all coverage data for the person.   The coverage detail is contained in the TierCoverage element.

No change to medical coverage

 

 

 

 

 

L.B. changes dental plan to ‘Employee and Spouse’ coverage effective 2004-04-01. Termination will still be effective as of 2004-05-01.

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

Begin Employment:  The Employment element encapsulates indicative data describing L.B’s employment statuses.

L.B is an Active employee.

 

End Employment

Begin Dependent: Dependent data is encapsulated within the Subscriber element. The relationshipCode for this dependent is ‘Spouse’.

Begin Person:  Dependents also have a Person element that can contain the same elements as the Subscriber’s Person Element.

The dependent’s name is Shelley Preston. Her social security number is 999-51-2346.

 

 

 

 

Shelley’s Date of Birth is 1970-10-25.

End Person

Begin Coverage:  The Coverage Element encapsulates coverage data.  Here this element is encapsulated within the Dependent element, so it contains coverage data specific to the dependent.

 

Shelley is added to the ‘Employee and Spouse’ dental plan effective 2004-04-01.

 

 

 

 

End Coverage

End Dependent

End Subscriber

End Organization

End Enrollment
